Telegram Poll Bot
=================

This repository contains a small Telegram poll bot. To run it safely you should store sensitive configuration (API tokens, DB URLs, etc.) in a local `.env` file rather than committing them into source control.

Create your own .env file
-------------------------

1. Copy the example env file to a new local `.env` file:

   cp .env.example .env

2. Edit `.env` and replace placeholder values with your credentials.

3. Do NOT commit your `.env` file. Add `.env` to your `.gitignore` if it's not already ignored.


Create a zip file to upload to lambda
-------------------------
1. Run this command to download all the requirements: `pip install -r requirements.txt -t python`
2. Run this command to zip everything up: `mkdir -p python && cp bot_v0.py python && zip -r ../lambda_function.zip .`


Deployment
-------------------------
This is deployed in a Lambda function behind an API Gateway